title.narrative: IR 2.5 REPONSE AUX URGENCES EDUCATION

description.narrative: IR 2.5: In emergency situations , girls and boys have safe access to quality education, which contributes to Education In Emergencies, Equitable Access To Quality Education. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: UNIVERSAL QUALITY BASIC EDUCATIONPCR 2: By the end of 2018, universal access to education, and a significant and fair increase in completion of quality primary education, supported by a life-cycle approach, will be provided to children.

title.narrative: IR 2.5: In emergency situations , girls and boys have safe access to quality education

description.narrative: From January to November 2019, 257,313 children (133,827 girls) aged 5-17 years, affected by conflict or natural disasters, were given access to quality education. This includes, remedial courses, catch up courses and psychosocial support. Improvement in cluster coordination at national level has been put in place through trainings at national level with the participation of provincial actors. Regional clusters and Education in Emergency local groups had been keen to give more information from the field. As part of the response to school attacks, 64 schools have been built with 54 others in progress. | Status:Met | As-of Date:07/02/2020
